mentor-top-section\" data-id=\"565a82c8\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1c24ceba elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column\" data-id=\"1c24ceba\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap  elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-73934313 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"73934313\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\"><p><a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1043 size-large\" src=\"http://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Global-Game-Jam-Poster-copy2-713x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"862\" srcset=\"https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Global-Game-Jam-Poster-copy2-713x1024.jpg 713w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Global-Game-Jam-Poster-copy2-209x300.jpg 209w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Global-Game-Jam-Poster-copy2-768x1103.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p><p>\u00a0</p><p>This year we&#8217;re excited to be partnering with <a href=\"http://illuminations.uci.edu/events/2018_1_26_Global_Game_Jam.html\">UCI Illuminations</a>, <a href=\"http://ithrivegames.org/\">iThrive Games</a>, <a href=\"http://www.igdaoc.org/\">The IGDA of Orange County</a>, and <a href=\"http://clubs.uci.edu/vgdc/home.php\">UCI&#8217;s Video Game Development Club</a> for the Global Game Jam.</p><h1><a href=\"https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/\"><img class=\"wp-image-995 alignleft\" src=\"http://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/TPL-Logo-BW-words-transparent-1-300x188.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"172\" height=\"108\" srcset=\"https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/TPL-Logo-BW-words-transparent-1-300x188.png 300w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/TPL-Logo-BW-words-transparent-1-768x481.png 768w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/TPL-Logo-BW-words-transparent-1-1024x641.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 172px) 100vw, 172px\" /></a><a href=\"http://illuminations.uci.edu/\"><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://illuminations.uci.edu/img/Identity/Illuminations_Graphic_Element_Slider_2.gif\" alt=\"UCI Illuminations\" width=\"214\" height=\"107\" /></a><a href=\"http://ithrivegames.org/\"><img class=\"wp-image-993 alignleft\" src=\"http://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Itrive-1-261x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"95\" height=\"109\" srcset=\"https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Itrive-1-261x300.png 261w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Itrive-1-768x881.png 768w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Itrive-1-892x1024.png 892w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/Itrive-1.png 1478w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 95px) 100vw, 95px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.igdaoc.org/\"><img class=\"\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1479699562/IGDA_OC_Twitter_400x400.jpg\" alt=\"IGDA Orange County\" width=\"119\" height=\"119\" /></a><a href=\"http://clubs.uci.edu/vgdc/home.php\"><img class=\"alignleft\" src=\"http://clubs.uci.edu/vgdc/img/vgdc_logo.png\" width=\"128\" height=\"110\" /></a></h1><h1>\u00a0\u00a0Information for Jammers</h1><h1><a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1003\" src=\"http://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/ggj17_website_presskitheader-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" srcset=\"https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/ggj17_website_presskitheader-300x169.jpg 300w, https://transformativeplay.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/transformativeplay/uploads/ggj17_website_presskitheader.jpg 568w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></h1><ul><li><b>Registration: </b>All Jammers\u00a0<a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine\">should register on the GGJ website</a>. \u00a0If you register, and then decide that you don&#8217;t want to participate this weekend for any reason, please remove yourself from the site.</li><li><b>Code of Conduct:\u00a0</b>The UCI GGJ site is an inclusive environment that welcomes a diverse group of participants!\u00a0<a href=\"http://globalgamejam.org/code-conduct-legal-policies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://globalgamejam.org/code-conduct-legal-policies&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFvnitboUC4S4FzkK0bCaHymLDfvg\">\u00a0Please read and abide by the official GGJ Code of Conduct.</a>\u00a0 Please respect the facilities and clean up after yourselves as needed. We reserve the right remove jammers who violate either the letter or the spirit of this policy.</li><li><b>Parking: </b>While the GGJ at UCI is free for any and all participants, unfortunately parking is not. \u00a0<a href=\"https://www.parking.uci.edu/kioskmap/kioskmap.cfm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=https://www.parking.uci.edu/kioskmap/kioskmap.cfm&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHJr-IL8xKHFLNwgfMHWguAirqffw\">A map of parking kiosks and their hours can be found here.</a>\u00a0The closest parking garage is the Anteater Parking Structure, and the closest lot is Lot 12.\u00a0 Both require that you purchase a permit at a kiosk before you can park.\u00a0 Permits can be purchased for up to 24 hours at a time (the countdown starts when you purchase the permit) with a maximum cost of $14/24 hour period. We strongly encourage you to carpool with friends, or to take transit if possible.</li><li><b>Arrival and Keynote: </b>We will be checking people in at 4:30pm, outside of <a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/about/facilities/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.ics.uci.edu/about/facilities/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHgyVRNdIfX-1qKUwBkFz0gPXJ9jQ\">6011 in Donald Bren Hall</a>. The keynote will begin at 5pm, and will run for about an hour, followed by time to get into teams and meet people.\u00a0 Do not worry if you are going to arrive late &#8211; we won&#8217;t turn anyone away tonight! Along with the Keynote we will also reveal the official Theme for this year&#8217;s jam.\u00a0 Please do not post or transmit the theme to anyone outside of our site until the final keynote in Hawaii is finished.</li><li><b>Overnight Hours: </b>This year we are experimenting with keeping the site open for the full 48 hours of the jam. While we encourage everyone to go home and sleep for at least 6 hours, we will not be kicking anyone out.\u00a0 We will have some spaces designated as quite/dark areas for people who want to catch a quick nap without going home, so if you think you&#8217;re going to crash here be sure to bring a sleeping bag, and/or some pillows.</li><li><b>Meals and Snacks: </b>As with previous years, we will be providing a vast array of snacks and drinks.\u00a0 We will not be providing full meals, but there are many places to eat nearby. Most notably, <a href=\"http://www.shopirvinecompany.com/centers/irvine/university-center\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.shopirvinecompany.com/centers/irvine/university-center&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFDwMGXzzo1GRWwZguhrAZDCAbAbw\">University Center</a>\u00a0is a short walk or drive from the jam site, and <a href=\"http://www.shopirvinecompany.com/centers/newport-beach/the-bluffs-shopping-center\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.shopirvinecompany.com/centers/newport-beach/the-bluffs-shopping-center&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNH9-8U529l1p3ZO1n4vbpWA4Et2Lg\">The Bluffs</a>\u00a0is a short drive away.</li><li><b>Internet Access</b>: We will be providing internet access via the UCI campus WiFi network. <a href=\"http://www.oit.uci.edu/mobile/registration/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.oit.uci.edu/mobile/registration/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1485032871138000&amp;usg=AFQjCNF01ZZI-PaNnTExWSacoOZmaqn2ew\">Information about registering your device is here.</a>\u00a0Please note that we cannot guarantee wired/ethernet connections in the rooms, so plan accordingly if you are bringing a desktop computer.</li></ul><h2>NEW FOR 2018: All Ages Jam Site!</h2><div id=\"m_3414615324170678180AppleMailSignature\">For those of you with kids, who know kids, who like kids, who know and like people with kids&#8230;the Global Game Jam is for them too!\u00a0 The young jammers site this year is at the Old Rec Center in UCI&#8217;s residential housing community Verano.</div><div><p><strong>Where:</strong> Old Rec Center @ Verano Place 3300 South Verano &#8211; Parking Lot #24</p><div>Drive straight in and the spots directly ahead are for the center (no parking permit needed for pick up/drop off) and your vehicle will be pointing directly at the Old Rec Center building<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">. Young Jammers still have to register at the official at the main GGJ page.\u00a0Participants interested in jamming at the All-Ages site should contact\u00a0 Marie\u00a0Tsaasan (<a style=\"color: #ff0000;\" href=\"mailto:tsaasan@uci.edu\">tsaasan@uci.edu</a>) directly after registering for the jam.</span></div><p><strong>Schedule:</strong></p></div><ul><li>On Friday: we will meet at the tables in front of the Old Rec Center at 4:30 pm to walk over to campus (Room 6011 of Donald Bren Hall) for the introduction presentation and this year\u2019s Keynote. This is a 15 minute walk</li><li>After the presentation we will walk back to the Old Rec Center and talk about what we heard and group together kids who want to do different roles for the Game Jam (artwork, logic coding, game logic design, testing, etc).</li><li>Afterward we will all go home for a good night\u2019s rest.</li><li>We convene on Saturday 7:15am \u2013 7:15pm, ready to Jam!</li><li>Mid-day we will take a break, walk back over the main Jam site to walk around and see what the other teams are up to. Pizza will be provided, we will walk over to Main Jam (on campus for lunch).</li><li>We come back Sunday 7:15am \u2013 3:15pm, finish our games, upload them to the GGJ website, and then walk over to the main Jam site to present our games.</li></ul><div id=\"m_3414615324170678180AppleMailSignature\">\u00a0</div><h2>Special iThrive Prize!</h2><p><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://ithrivegames.org/wp-content/themes/ithriveHTMLConversion/img/iThriveLogo_2017_147x63.png\" width=\"265\" height=\"112\" /></p><p><span class=\"il\">iThrive</span> <span class=\"il\">Games</span> exists to create meaningful experiences for teens that enhance the knowledge, mindsets, and skills they need to thrive through development and across the continuum of mental disorder to wellness. Across our initiatives, we co-design with teens and emphasize teen voice and accessible products and experiences. We consult with scholars in developmental science, neuroscience, learning science, and social psychology (among other fields) and consult with game developers and artificial intelligence experts to understand the complexities of creating meaningful player experiences and to facilitate the creation of transformative <span class=\"il\">games</span> that prioritize teens\u2019 developmental and mental health needs.</p><p><em><strong><a href=\"http://ithrivegames.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/iThrive-Designer-Guide-Kindness.pdf\">iThrive&#8217;s Diversifier is KINDNESS!</a></strong></em></p><p><em><strong><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1djOrw4ju-EPH-omngaM143fNdIGLv0ML/view?usp=sharing\">iThrive Games have provided a document to guide jammers when designing for their diversifier.</a></strong></em></p><p>This year, iThrive Games has generously sponsored the UCI GGJ site with a special prize for the top three games to use their diversifier. To be eligible for the prize, your game:</p><ul><li>Must use iThrive\u2019s Kindness diversifier</li><li>Must use iThrive\u2019s design resources</li><li>The game needs to be for a teen audience</li><li><em><strong><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScIscQigiqfQOT4axAsslFRpZgaDUg7Td5TRKLWg9NloG9VEg/viewform\">If you wish to compete for these prizes, please register your game here!</a></strong></em></li></ul><p><u>Questions or subject matter help?</u></p><p><b>Direct tweet our iThrive contact: @Death_Bow</b></p><p><img src=\"http://illuminations.uci.edu/img/2017_2018_Winter/Global_Game_Jam_Banner.jpg\" alt=\"Global Game Jam\" /></p><h1>FAQ&#8217;s</h1><h2>When is the Global Game Jam?</h2><p>The Global Game Jam runs for 48 hours, from January 26-28, 2018\u00a0 We will be starting our Jam at 5:00 pm on the 26th.</p><h2>Where is the Global Game Jam?</h2><p>The Jam site at UC Irvine\u00a0will be in Donald Bren Hall. Registration and Keynote are in room 6011.</p><h2>Who\u00a0can participate in the Jam?</h2><p>The UCI Global Game Jam site is open to to everyone with an interest in making games, not just UCI students. \u00a0We encourage participation from all potential Jammers from the broader games community at UCI including members of the games industry who are interested in a chance to do something wild and creative with their spare time. The Main Site is 18+, however we have a nearby all-ages site for minors who wish to Jam. If you are interested in participating in the all-ages site please <a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine\">register on our GGJ main page</a> and contact <a href=\"mailto:tsaasan@uci.edu\">tsaasan@uci.edu</a> for more information.</p><h2>Does the Jam cost anything?</h2><p>Nope &#8211; it&#8217;s free! If you are driving a car onto campus, you will have to pay for parking. \u00a0<a href=\"http://en.parkopedia.com/parking/garage/uci_anteater_parking_structure/92617/irvine/\">The nearest parking structure to the venue is the Anteater Parking Structure, which is $10 a day.</a>\u00a0We encourage ridesharing and carpooling.</p><h2>How can I participate in the Jam?</h2><p><strong><a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine\">Every Jammer needs to sign up for the Jam though the official GGJ website.</a>\u00a0<a href=\"https://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine\">http://globalgamejam.org/2018/jam-sites/uc-irvine</a></strong></p><h2>Should I come to the Jam with a team of \u00a0people I want to work with?</h2><p>Actually, part of the fun of the Jam is getting a chance to connect with other designers and gamers, so we strongly discourage doing any teambuilding before arrival. \u00a0Think of the Jam as a chance to stretch yourself, to meet new people, and to explore game design ideas that you might not get to explore under other circumstances. \u00a0The GGJ is a great environment to take risks and learn new things, and there is usually a very broad range of skills and talent in the room to work with. \u00a0We have found it helpful to arrive with a sense of what you are interested in doing: are you a writer? an artist? a programmer? a designer? a musician? a playtester? \u00a0You don\u2019t have to be an expert at any of these things to have a good time, although it is very helpful to be at least familiar with games, and to have some experience with either game design, or with production and development more broadly. \u00a0We will do our best to match people up into teams that have a good balance of skills and experience, so that everyone has a chance to succeed, but it is important to remember that the central objective of the GJJ is\u00a0to find the fun in game design.</p><h2>What if I\u2019m not a programmer? \u00a0Can I participate in the the Jam?</h2><p>Games require a very broad range of skills and abilities: not just programming. \u00a0We\u2019ve been to game jams where none of the participants were programmers, and all of the games that were made were pen &amp; paper games, card games, and board games. \u00a0Chances are there will be many people at the Jam with programming skills, but also plenty of people there who are good at other things. \u00a0Everyone should be able to participate in a meaningful way, and we will work to help you find a spot where you can make a contribution.</p><h2>Can I bring a work in progress to the Jam?</h2><p>No. \u00a0Technically we have no way to stop you from doing this, but it isn\u2019t really in the spirit of the event. \u00a0This is why we have an inspirational keynote at the beginning, and a top secret theme that we don\u2019t reveal until you arrive. \u00a0The goal is for people to imagine and create a new game from nothing in a weekend.</p><h2>What happens to the games after the Jam?</h2><p>One of the conditions of participating in the Global Game Jam is that\u00a0any games you make on the weekend are Open Source, and shared on the <a href=\"http://globalgamejam.org/2014/games\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GGJ repository.</a>\u00a0 This is another reason why Jammers are discouraged from bringing existing works and intellectual property. \u00a0The GGJ as an organization isn\u2019t interested in getting involved in any IP disputes over copyright or ownership. \u00a0We also want to make the jam a safe place for professionals within the industry to express their creativity without creating\u00a0any conflict-of-interest with their day-jobs and employers.</p><h2>What Should I Bring to the Jam?</h2><p>We will be providing the following:</p><ul><li>Internet Access for all Jammers</li><li>Power for computers, laptops, chargers, equipment, etc.</li><li>A space, and tables and chairs to work at.</li><li>Snacks and beverages.</li><li>Sleeping Bags, Pillows, and other comfy things.</li></ul><p>Jammers should plan to bring anything that they think they might need to make their games. \u00a0This could include\u00a0computer systems with appropriate development tools and software installed, sketching and art supplies for brainstorming and concept development,\u00a0audio recording gear and music making tools, dice, cards,\u00a0tablets, styli, and any other creative tools that you use or would like to use to help create your games.</p></div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t                            </div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\n\n                                                    </article><!-- #post-## -->\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n\n\n\t\t\n\t</main>\n</div>\n\n\n\t<!-- Begin Footer Section -->\n\t<footer id=\"footer\">\n        <div class=\"container\">\n            <div class=\"row\">\n                            </div>\n\n                    <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"copyrights\">\n              